  "texts": [
    "Due to limitations of the human body and mind, people may not be able to satisfyingly fulfill the standards set by AI partners or friends.",
    "While of course these chatbots (for now) lack corporeal substance and therefore cannot fulfill some concluded through a series of experiments assessing ethical judgement and moral dilemma scenarios [70].of the most crucial aspects of human relationships relating to touch and presence [71], [72], [73], they certainly can fulfill many other aspects of social engagement, and even enable users to play out both prospective and entirely fantastical scenarios [74].Additionally, social chatbots represent a direct sort of \"quantification\" of relationships-complete, in some cases, with actual rewards for good behavior.",
    "Replika released a feature in 2023 called \"Relationship Bond,\" which they noted was \"not only to promote constructive social interactions but also to guide future model training toward an even safer and more ethical path\" [75].",
    "By offering users rewards for treating their Replikas well, they intended to instill better values and behaviors.",
    "However, we could not help but notice that this process actually mirrors the process of LLM training (rewarding certain responses)."
